div.p:
Iob. 5. v. 3, I have seene, said Eliphaz, the foolish
taking roote: but tooke hee root for to continue? No, not: Suddainlie, said hee, I cursed his habitation: incontinent his children for whose standing and preferment hee solde himselfe to wickednesse were crushed in the gate;
Iob. 5. v. 4. neither was there any to deliver them. As for their harvest and expected crop, others did devoure it, not leaving them the miserable stalkes which grew among the thornes. v. 5.


   Note.
This was the practise of Joseph while his Mistresse saide to him; lye with mee;
   Gen. 39. v. 9 hee cryed vnto God. How should I doe this wickednesse; and sinne against God?
